<TITLE> 3 National Museum galleries shut down for 'wrong history' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 05 (bdnews24.com)An information ministry order on Sunday shut down three galleries of the National Museum for an indefinite period 'to preserve the correct history of the liberation war'. The decision was taken in presence of information and cultural affairs minister Abul Kalam Azad, said a statement of the ministry. "Galleries 38, 39 and 40 will be closed until further notice," said the statement. It said the decision was taken to ensure the true history of the liberation war was portrayed. "The authentic history and memorabilia of the liberation war will soon be restored in the three mentioned galleries," it said. bdnew
